[src:analytic-number-theory/dirichlet-series] The formal Dirichlet series form a ring Ω, indeed an *R*-algebra, with the zero function as additive zero element and the function *δ* defined by *δ*(1) = 1, *δ*(*n*) = 0 for *n* > 1 as multiplicative identity.
