[src:analytic-number-theory/prime-counting-function] In 1959, Derrick Henry Lehmer extended and simplified Meissel's method.
[src:analytic-number-theory/prime-counting-function] Define, for real m and for natural numbers n and k, *Pk*(*m*,*n*) as the number of numbers not greater than m with exactly k prime factors, all greater than pn.
