[src:analytic-number-theory/prime-counting-function] Formulas for prime-counting functions come in two kinds: arithmetic formulas and analytic formulas.
[src:analytic-number-theory/prime-counting-function] Analytic formulas for prime-counting were the first used to prove the prime number theorem.
[src:analytic-number-theory/prime-counting-function] They stem from the work of Riemann and von Mangoldt, and are generally known as explicit formulae.
